B.nJ=s(["Urban Warmth","Dark Mode","Organic Warmth","Street"],t.s)
B.a4_=s(["1x","2x","3x","0.5x"],t.s)
B.a40=s(["Effects","Filters","Beauty","Timer"],t.s)
B.a5K=s(["Authenticity","Confidence","Approachability"],t.s)
B.M7=new A.dk("Warm & Grounding",B.a5K,"Terracotta and earth tones activate warmth associations rooted in natural materials \u2014 clay, leather, sun-baked stone. Research shows warm hues increase perceived friendliness and reduce social distance. The sage green secondary adds a trust-anchoring organic quality.","Analogous + Accent","Terracotta, amber, and sage sit near each other on the warm side of the wheel, creating cohesion while sage provides a natural contrast point.","Dating and social profiles where genuine, confident first impressions matter more than flashy design.","Dark brown text on warm cream provides strong readability. The terracotta accent meets AA contrast on white surfaces.",'Earth tones feel premium without trying too hard \u2014 the palette says "I have taste" without shouting. Sage green verified badges feel organic and trustworthy.',"The warm overlay tints photos with terracotta which may not complement every skin tone. Limited cool tones make the palette feel heavy in large surfaces.")
B.a4K=s(["Sophistication","Trust","Exclusivity"],t.s)
B.Mh=new A.dk("Elegant & Refined",B.a4K,"Champagne gold and burgundy are historically associated with wealth and fine craftsmanship. Gold activates reward centers \u2014 studies show it increases perceived value of adjacent elements. The muted burgundy prevents ostentation, keeping luxury quiet rather than loud.","Complementary","Warm gold and cool burgundy sit on opposite sides of the wheel, creating visual tension that reads as sophisticated contrast.","Premium product showcases, luxury dating experiences, and editorial content where the audience expects refinement.","Near-black text on cream background exceeds AAA contrast. Gold accents need careful sizing to maintain readability at small scales.","The restrained palette signals quality through subtlety \u2014 like a well-designed hotel lobby. Every colour earns its place.",'Can feel muted or "beige" to younger demographics expecting bolder visual energy. Burgundy on gold can look dated if proportions are off.')
B.a43=s(["Excitement","Fun","Playfulness"],t.s)
B.M3=new A.dk("Bold & Energetic",B.a43,"Electric blue and hot pink trigger dopamine-associated excitement responses. High-saturation colours demand attention \u2014 the brain processes them 20% faster than muted tones. The multi-chromatic approach mirrors Gen Z visual language shaped by social media.","Triadic","Blue, pink, and green form an equilateral triangle on the colour wheel, maximising vibrancy while maintaining mathematical balance.","Youth-oriented social feeds, gamified experiences, and content discovery where energy and engagement are the priority.","White text on saturated blue/pink passes AA. The high saturation can cause visual fatigue in extended reading \u2014 use neutrals for body text.","Instantly eye-catching and impossible to scroll past. The palette practically vibrates with youthful energy and makes UI feel alive.","Risk of visual overwhelm \u2014 too many saturated elements competing for attention. Needs generous neutral space to breathe.")
B.a44=s(["Focus","Modernity","Immersion"],t.s)
B.M5=new A.dk("Mysterious & Premium",B.a44,"True black backgrounds with purple accents evoke digital-native luxury. Purple has the shortest wavelength in visible light, activating creative and contemplative neural pathways. Dark UIs reduce eye strain in low-light and create a cinema-like focus on content.","Analogous","Purple, cyan, and pink occupy adjacent cool positions, unified by their luminous quality against the dark background.","Night-time browsing, media-heavy feeds, dating apps where mood and atmosphere matter more than information density.","White text on true black achieves maximum 21:1 contrast ratio. Purple accents need sufficient brightness to read against dark surfaces.","The dark canvas makes every color pop like neon signs. Content feels curated and cinematic, photos look their absolute best.",'True black OLED smearing on scroll. Extended dark-mode use can feel oppressive \u2014 no warm "breathing room" for the eyes.')
B.a3V=s(["Comfort","Trust","Wellness"],t.s)
B.Mi=new A.dk("Natural & Nurturing",B.a3V,"Terracotta paired with sage green mirrors natural landscapes \u2014 research in biophilic design shows these combinations reduce cortisol levels by 8-12%. The warm cream background emulates natural paper, creating a tactile quality that digital screens usually lack.","Analogous","Earth-toned palette stays within a 90-degree arc of warm hues, creating deep harmony reminiscent of autumn landscapes.","Wellness content, mindful dating, organic marketplace listings, and any context where calm authenticity builds trust.","Warm dark brown on cream meets AAA at body sizes. Terracotta on white passes AA. Sage green needs a dark background for text readability.","Feels like holding a handmade ceramic mug \u2014 warm, textured, and genuinely comforting. The organic palette ages gracefully.","Can read as conservative or earthy-crunchy to some demographics. Limited punch for attention-grabbing CTAs in competitive feeds.")
B.a6w=s(["Clarity","Efficiency","Professionalism"],t.s)
B.Mg=new A.dk("Precise & Authoritative",B.a6w,"The Swiss design tradition eliminates decoration to let information speak. Red accents exploit the urgency response \u2014 red processing is fastest among all hues. Black on white is the highest-contrast pairing possible, maximising scanning speed and comprehension.","Monochromatic + Accent","Black-white backbone with a single red accent creates maximum visual hierarchy from minimum elements.","Information-dense interfaces, professional profiles, marketplace listings where clarity and scannability are paramount.","Black on white is 21:1 \u2014 the theoretical maximum. Red on white at large sizes passes AA. System requires no contrast workarounds.","Aggressively functional \u2014 nothing competes with content. The red accent has maximum stopping power because there is zero colour noise.","Can feel clinical or cold for intimate contexts like dating. No emotional warmth \u2014 every surface is a working surface.")
B.a42=s(["Energy","Locality","Authenticity"],t.s)
B.Ml=new A.dk("Raw & Urban",B.a42,"Red signals urgency and passion \u2014 street culture leverages this for immediacy. Blue-grey secondary provides trust-anchoring calm, a counterweight seen in urban signage systems worldwide. Orange tertiary brings warmth without softening the edge.","Split-Complementary","Red primary with blue-grey and warm orange flanking its complement, creating dynamic tension without the harshness of pure complements.","Location-based discovery, neighbourhood social feeds, street market browsing \u2014 anything rooted in local culture and immediacy.","Dark text on warm off-white meets AAA. Red accents are strong on white but need size considerations on the warm background.","Feels like a well-designed street poster \u2014 bold, immediate, and impossible to ignore. The warm paper tone grounds the energy.","Red fatigue in heavy usage \u2014 too many red elements reduce urgency effectiveness. The palette can feel aggressive in quieter contexts.")
B.a4x=s(["Peace","Creativity","Mindfulness"],t.s)
B.M8=new A.dk("Soft & Serene",B.a4x,'Lavender activates the parasympathetic nervous system, lowering heart rate and blood pressure. Combined with mint green and soft pink, this triadic palette creates what neuroscientists call "soft fascination" \u2014 engaged attention without cognitive load.',"Triadic (Pastel)","Purple, green, and pink form an equilateral triangle, but at low saturation the contrast is gentle rather than jarring.","Meditation content, thoughtful social connections, wellness features, and any UI that wants to feel calming yet modern.","Grey text on near-white passes AA at body sizes. Lavender accents are subtle \u2014 critical actions may need darker variants for clickability.","Uniquely calming in a world of bold apps \u2014 the pastel palette feels like a deep breath. Distinctively modern without being harsh.","Low contrast pastels can wash out on cheaper screens. The softness may not convey enough urgency for marketplace or competitive dating.")
